item.title: Web hosting
item.dc:creator: @The_Un-Named The Un-Named
item.description:
@The_Un-Named wrote:

[quote=“bam bam, post:10, topic:11261”][quote author=gikid link=topic=16778.msg191085#msg191085 date=1156749420]
he’s a windows user
[/quote]
hahaha ROLF but not all windows users are complete idiots, Just cheap…[/quote]

Oh, so now linux cd’s are £100? So are you an idiot now?

I run windows because my pc came with it, not once have I seen a computer shop that sells computers running linux. Yes, online maybe but as a first time computer buyer, your probally going to get a windows/mac.

I don’t see how you can call windows users cheap, I mean like almost all the software that came with my pc made it cost alot, infact I’m probally paying more for windows & it’s software than my computer hardware it’s self. Linux, however, is completly freeware. It’s free, if you don’t want to use it no one is forcing you to use it. IF you want to buy a computer, you CAN’T buy a computer with no OS installed, and you probally will need to buy a computer with mac/windows installed, as there probally the most common OSs.

ALL the linux users I know did start off with a windows computer. My teacher for example started with a windows computer and his new pc did come with windows, he dose use windows for teaching. If I brought a pc with linux installed as a primary OS installed, and I used linux for 5 seconds, it dose not make me a super leet haxx0r. Comming back to the starting sence of this paragraph, most linux users probally did start from windows, and probally did have a hard time with windows to encourage them to actually learn about OSs and make them switch to an OS that dosen’t have a gazillion viruses/spyware/popups.

Ohh yeah, as far as I’m conserned, you started the topic looking for a web host, seen someone being taught a lesson and someone tauting them and you went along, why didn’t you just host your own webspace/server insted of making this topic, or are you an idiot?
